    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-09T06:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-09T06:54:00-05:00" n="804"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/9–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-09T15:00:00+03:06"
                            >September 9, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>273. While Saudi Government should be informed without delay of increase in food
                    subsidy (re Legation’s 270, September 8, 2 p.m. paragraph 1) this communication
                    should be shortly followed by reply to King’s demand for return of 1943
                    pilgrimage revenues (re Legation’s 235, August 6, 10 a.m. paragraph 4). King
                    expects full reply <pb facs="0750" n="738" xml:id="pg_738"/> to that
                    communication be made to both Governments. Hope Department can insist on reply
                    by British. It concerns us because (1) affects Saudi finances and (2) demand
                    addressed to US as well as British. Reply to King should be before Jordan leaves
                    September 15 on 6-week vacation.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
